com.jnape.palatable.lambda.functions

Interface Fn3<A,B,C,D>

  • Type Parameters:
    A - The first argument type
    B - The second argument type
    C - The third argument type
    D - The return type
    All Superinterfaces:
    Applicative<Fn1<B,Fn1<C,D>>,Fn1<A,?>>, Fn1<A,Fn1<B,Fn1<C,D>>>, Fn2<A,B,Fn1<C,D>>, Function<A,Fn1<B,Fn1<C,D>>>, Functor<Fn1<B,Fn1<C,D>>,Fn1<A,?>>, Profunctor<A,Fn1<B,Fn1<C,D>>,Fn1>
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    BiMonoidFactory<A,B,C>, BiSemigroupFactory<A,B,C>, Fn4<A,B,C,D,E>, MonoidFactory<A,B>, SemigroupFactory<A,B>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AddAll, Collapse, Collapse, FoldLeft, FoldRight, LeftAll, LeftAll, LeftAny, LeftAny, Merge, Merge, Over, Present, RightAll, RightAll, RightAny, RightAny, ScanLeft, Set, ZipWith
    Functional Interface:
    This is a functional interface and can therefore be used as the assignment target for a lambda expression or method reference.

    @FunctionalInterface
public interface Fn3<A,B,C,D>
extends Fn2<A,B,Fn1<C,D>>
    A function taking three arguments. Defined in terms of Fn2, so similarly auto-curried.
